## Must Review In GitHub Variables

These were uploaded with placeholder values and must be replaced before AWS deployment:

```text
AWS_DEV_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN
AWS_STAGING_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN
AWS_PROD_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN
AWS_TERRAFORM_PLAN_ROLE_ARN
ECS_SUBNET_IDS
ECS_SECURITY_GROUP_IDS
WEBHOOK_VERIFY_URL
SYNTHETIC_WEBHOOK_URL
```

Also confirm these match your actual AWS resources:

```text
APP_URL
ECR_REPOSITORY
ECS_CLUSTER
ECS_WEB_SERVICE
ECS_WORKER_SERVICE
ECS_WEB_TASK_FAMILY
ECS_WORKER_TASK_FAMILY
```

## Production Safety

Keep this value false until a test signup has been verified end to end:

```text
WHATSAPP_CREATE_REAL_PROFILE=false
```

After staging/test signup writes correctly to the existing `register` table, change production to:

```text
WHATSAPP_CREATE_REAL_PROFILE=true
```

## Media Storage Choice

If ECS can write to the same website storage path:

```text
MEDIA_STORAGE_DRIVER=legacy_public_user
WHATSAPP_ONBOARDING_LOCAL_MEDIA_PATH=storage/user
WHATSAPP_ONBOARDING_MEDIA_DB_VALUE=filename_only
```

If ECS is separate and cannot share `public/storage/user`, change to S3:

```text
MEDIA_STORAGE_DRIVER=s3
AWS_S3_MEDIA_PREFIX=nxtutors/onboarding
```

Then add the S3 bucket secrets listed above.

## Do Not Add

Do not add long-lived AWS access keys to GitHub:

```text
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
```

Use GitHub OIDC with AWS role ARN variables instead.

Do not create Lambda for the main agent:

```text
CREATE_LAMBDA_FUNCTION=false
DEPLOY_TARGET=ecs
```

## Tutor "Pro Mode" (paid AI profile)

> IMPORTANT — where config actually takes effect:
> Your live deploy is **CloudPanel** (`.github/workflows/deploy-cloudpanel.yml`). It rsyncs files
> over SSH and **excludes `.env`**, so the running app reads config from the **server `.env`**, NOT
> from GitHub secrets/variables. GitHub Environment secrets only feed the (currently unused) AWS ECS
> workflows. **So to turn Pro Mode on for the live site, edit the server `.env` below.** The GitHub
> entries are only needed if/when you deploy via AWS.

### A) Server `.env` (CloudPanel — THIS is what enables Pro mode)

Add these to the same server `.env` that already holds your `DB_*` / `META_*` values. On the
CloudPanel box that is one of (first that exists wins, per `load_onboarding_env()`):

```text
/home/nxtutors-onboarding/htdocs/onboarding.nxtutors.com/public/.env
/home/nxtutors-onboarding/htdocs/onboarding.nxtutors.com/.env
/home/nxtutors-onboarding/htdocs/onboarding.nxtutors.com/nx-whatsapp-onboarding-agent/.env
```

Edit it via CloudPanel File Manager or SSH and append:

```env
# --- Tutor Pro Mode ---
# Keep PRO_MODE_ENABLED=false until the Razorpay keys below are filled & tested.
PRO_MODE_ENABLED=false
PRO_MODE_PRICE_INR=10
PRO_MODE_BASE_URL=https://onboarding.nxtutors.com

# Razorpay (LEAVE for you to fill — money settles to the bank/UPI in your Razorpay dashboard).
# Use test-mode keys first. Webhook URL to register in Razorpay: https://onboarding.nxtutors.com/pro/webhook (event: payment.captured)
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=
RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# OpenAI (the GitHub OPENAI_API_KEY does NOT reach CloudPanel — set it here on the server too).
OPENAI_API_KEY=
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o

# Private storage (must be writable by the web user; outside the public/ web root).
PRO_DIR=/home/nxtutors-onboarding/onboarding-data/pro
PRO_CV_DIR=/home/nxtutors-onboarding/onboarding-data/cv
PRO_CV_MAX_KB=5120
PRO_WHATSAPP_CONFIRM=true
```

After filling the Razorpay + OpenAI values and confirming one test signup, set
`PRO_MODE_ENABLED=true`. Also raise the CloudPanel site's PHP upload limits
(`upload_max_filesize` / `post_max_size`) to ~8M for CV uploads.

### B) GitHub (only for the AWS workflow path — add these yourself in the UI)

I could not add these from here (this CLI token has `push` but not `admin`; only the repo owner can
edit Actions secrets/variables). Add as repo **Variables**:

```text
PRO_MODE_ENABLED=false
PRO_MODE_PRICE_INR=10
PRO_MODE_BASE_URL=https://onboarding.nxtutors.com
OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o
PRO_DIR=/var/run/nxtutors-onboarding/pro
PRO_CV_DIR=/var/run/nxtutors-onboarding/cv
PRO_CV_MAX_KB=5120
PRO_WHATSAPP_CONFIRM=true
```

Add as repo/Environment **Secrets** (Razorpay left blank for you; OpenAI key already added):

```text
RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=          # you will fill
RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=      # you will fill
RAZORPAY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=  # you will fill
# OPENAI_API_KEY already exists
```
